  "profile": "Solo Agency and Promoters was formed in 1986 to represent artists for their UK and international touring. The original client roster was founded on the early 80's success of Big Country, Paul Young, Alison Moyet and Howard Jones combined with the New York punk of Iggy Pop and The Ramones. Its first 'premier league' breakthrough was promoting David Bowie at Wembley Stadium in 1986, to be followed by the signing of Phil Collins and Genesis 2 years later.",
